Name: Description
Resident Jobs:
Industry number and percentages refer to the total and share of workers (aged 16 and over) in an industry, by the residence of the jobholder. CCC generated 5-year estimates and coded this variable to correspond with broader categories outlined by the North American Industry Classification System. 

"Management and Professional Services" includes workers in Legal Services, Scientific Research and Development, Architectural and Engineering Services, and other professions which tend to require advanced degrees or certificates.

"Other Services" includes workers in Auto Repair and Maintenance, Barber Shops, Beauty Salons, and Religious Organizations, among others.

Workers in the Agricultural, Extraction, and Utilities industries, as well as those employed by the military, make up less than 0.5% of the citywide population of workers and are omitted from the data.

Name: Source Notes
Resident Jobs: U.S. Census Bureau, American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates, Table S2403 (2010, 2015, 2020, 2021); retrieved from https://data.census.gov/.

Name: Notes
Resident Jobs: According to the Census Bureau, overlapping datasets should not be compared. To track change over time compare non-overlapping datasets, such as  2010-2015 ACS 5-year estimates compared to 2016-2020 ACS 5-year estimates.
